wikipedia_page.main: George Cornwall Legh JP DL MP (30 August 1804 – 16 June 1877) was a 19th-century British Conservative Member of Parliament who represented Mid Cheshire.

List of MPs elected in the 1868 United Kingdom general election

response: The Cheshire Mid by-election of 1873 was contested on 7 March 1873, due to  the resignation of the incumbent Conservative MP, George Legh. It was won by the Conservative candidate Egerton Leigh.
